      <h2 class="lesson-header">What is a light curve?</h2>  
      <p class='lesson-text'>
        A light curve is a plot of a particular star's brightness over time. If you stare at a star long enough (not recommended) you may notice that it's brightness changes. This may be because the star's brightness is simply variable -- such stars are appropriately called variable stars. But on rare occasions, the changes in brightness may be due to an actual planet passing, or <i>transiting</i>, in front of it. This results in a slight dip in the brightness as the planet covers the incoming light. BAM! Consider yourself schooled.
      </p>
